The paper discusses machine intelligence systems and their reliance on gradient-based learning through backpropagation. This places it in the realm of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, the paper deals with unsupervised learning and likelihood functions, which are common topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses GANs, which are a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper introduces a new tool for optimizing implicit likelihoods, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound).
